-- Nadal Outlasts Berdych to Reach Australian Open Semifinal Against Federer
-- B y   D a n   B a y n e s
-- 2012-01-24T13:01:33Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-01-24/nadal-outlasts-berdych-to-reach-australian-open-semifinal-against-federer.html
No. 2 seed  Rafael Nadal  fought back
to beat seventh-seededTomas Berdych in four sets and set up an
Australian Open semifinal againstRoger Federer.  Nadal of Spain won 6-7 (5-7), 7-6 (8-6), 6-4, 6-3 to reach
the final four at Melbourne Park for the first time since 2009,
when he took the title with a five-set win over Federer. He’s
bidding to win his 11th major championship.  Nadal outlasted Berdych in a 4 hour, 16 minute-match on Rod
Laver Arena that finished at midnight local time.    Federer earlier beat No. 11 seed Juan Martin Del Potro of
Argentina in straight sets. Women’s defending champion  Kim Clijsters  of Belgium and third-seeded Belarusian Victoria
Azarenka also won to advance to a semifinal meeting.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Dan Baynes at 
 dbaynes@bloomberg.net  